summaries.full: 1998: A car accident lands Gennaro "Jerry" Colombo in the ICU, leading Jerome "Jerry" Jacobson to scout for new recruiters. Among those who join are ex-con Andrew Glomb and Mormon real estate developer Dwight Baker, who convinces his foster son George Chandler to redeem a winning ticket. Meanwhile, the FBI's "Operation: Final Answer" gains speed.

summaries.short: The FBI intercepts a call with "Uncle Jerry" that leads them to capture crucial evidence of a game piece exchange.
summaries.full: Focusing their attention on Dwight Baker, the FBI intercepts a call with "Uncle Jerry" that leads them to capture crucial evidence of a game piece exchange. With the latest Monopoly game drawing to an end, the FBI works overtime to launch a coordinated cross-country day of indictments, though a last-minute technical error threatens to upend their carefully-laid plans.

summaries.short: Gloria Brown's connection to the scheme is revealed, as the Colombos diversify the ticket operation under building pressure.
summaries.full: Frank Colombo, the brother of "Jerry" Colombo, reveals the inner workings of the scam whereby "Uncle Jerry" would sell winning tickets to Gennaro "Jerry" Colombo for a premium. Colombo would then find willing takers in exchange for a cut of the prize money. Meanwhile, the undercover FBI video crew interviews Gloria Brown, a million-dollar "winner" in South Carolina.

summaries.short: The FBI investigates two prominent figures in the scam, hoping to identify one of them as the mysterious "Uncle Jerry."
summaries.full: Hoping to unmask "Uncle Jerry," the FBI investigates two figures they believe are connected to the scam. The first, Jerome "Jerry" Jacobson, is a former cop working security for Simon Marketing, the company hired to run the McDonald's Monopoly game. The second, Gennaro "Jerry" Colombo, hails from a notorious East Coast mob family and is no stranger to unsavory activities.
